    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 12,
        "summary": "A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband\u2014The way of a fool is right in his own eyes\u2014Lying lips are an abomination to the Lord.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge: but he that hateth reproof is brutish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Edification; Teachable.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 823
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A good man obtaineth favour of the Lord: but a man of wicked devices will he condemn.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 82:10.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man shall not be established by wickedness: but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband: but she that maketh ashamed is as rottenness in his bones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ruth 3:11. TG\u00a0Chastity; Virtue.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives; Woman.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The thoughts of the righteous are right: but the counsels of the wicked are deceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counselor.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The words of the wicked are to lie in wait for blood: but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked are overthrown, and are not: but the house of the righteous shall stand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:25.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 14:25 (24\u201327).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man shall be commended according to his wisdom: but he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is despised, and hath a servant, is better than he that honoureth himself, and lacketh bread.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:1 (1\u201310).",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A righteous man regardeth the life of his beast: but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:26; D&C 29:24 (24\u201325); 49:19 (18\u201321); 77:2; Moses 3:19.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Cruelty.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that tilleth his land shall be satisfied with bread: but he that followeth vain persons is void of understanding.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked desireth the net of evil men: but the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wicked is snared by the transgression of his lips: but the just shall come out of trouble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "James 3:13 (2\u201314). TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth: and the recompence of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of a fool is right in his own eyes: but he that hearkeneth unto counsel is wise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Problem-Solving.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 124:90 (89\u201390).",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool's wrath is presently known: but a prudent man covereth shame.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that speaketh truth sheweth forth righteousness: but a false witness deceit.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is that speaketh like the piercings of a sword: but the tongue of the wise is health.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The lip of truth shall be established for ever: but a lying tongue is but for a moment.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Deceit is in the heart of them that imagine evil: but to the counsellors of peace is joy.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There shall no evil happen to the just: but the wicked shall be filled with mischief.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Lying lips are abomination to the Lord: but they that deal truly are his delight.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A prudent man concealeth knowledge: but the heart of fools proclaimeth foolishness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The hand of the diligent shall bear rule: but the slothful shall be under tribute.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Diligence.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Heaviness in the heart of man maketh it stoop: but a good word maketh it glad.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous is more excellent than his neighbour: but the way of the wicked seduceth them.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The slothful man roasteth not that which he took in hunting: but the substance of a diligent man is precious.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Diligence.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the way of righteousness is life; and in the pathway thereof there is no death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}